args: Agh, n-no! If you open the lid...!
Okay, I think that's all of them.\nBut who put all those frogs there\nin the first place?
All I know is that it's an absolutely\nmalicious trick to play on someone.
Aw, Cleo! Did you look in the pot already?\nIt was supposed to be a surprise!
Of course! I even caught 'em myself.
I prepare meals for everyone here in this\nkitchen. It is my sanctuary. My oasis.
And if you are going to play pranks like\nsome foul devil, then you are hereby\nbanned from my kitchen for life!
Wait, are you MAD at me?!
This wasn't a devil trick, I swear!\nI worked really hard to catch all\nthose frogs for you!
You're mean, Cleo! I hate you!
As weird as this sounds, I think she\nhonestly thought you'd enjoy the frogs.
Let me go talk to her. Wait here, okay?
Cleo, you dummy... *sniffle*\nYou're such a stupid-head!
Talk to me about the frogs.

I know how to make a super tasty frog
casserole and I was gonna surprise Cleo
by making it but she's a big stupid-face
and so now I totally don't wanna!
Everyone in my tribe LOVES my\nfrog casserole, and I thought it\nwould make Cleo happy.
But instead she's just all mad...
Frog...casserole? Er, I mean,\nthat's a very nice thought, Yue.
But Cleo just misunderstood—she thought\nyou were playing a prank on her.
Whaaat?! Who hates FROGS?!\nThey're so tasty and easy to catch!
That's, um... Well, I guess different people\njust like different things sometimes.
And since Cleo hates frogs, she instantly\nthought someone was playing a mean\nprank on her.
If you clear up the misunderstanding,\nI'm sure the two of you can make up.\nSo let's head back to the kitchen, okay?
...Wait. So you were actually going to\ncook the frogs for me as a surprise?
Yeah. I wasn't trying to scare you,\nand I'm really sorry if I did.
I think I am the one who needs\nto apologize here.
I let myself become angry without\nfully understanding the situation.
Disliking frogs is my issue, and I took it\nout on you.
Thus, I was in the wrong, and for that,\nI am sorry.
Please refrain from leaping on me.
Ha ha! Looks like you're friends again.\nAlthough I have to say, Cleo, I had\nno idea you hated frogs so much.
I'm not proud, but I've been terrified of the\ncreatures for as long as I can remember.
Well, the next time frogs show up,\nI'll totally protect you!
I'm gonna figure out a way for you to\nenjoy my famous frog casserole!
I know you're scared of them, but a\nfrog casserole totally can't hurt you!
I think you misunderstand my\nobjection to this plan.
I mean, fiends are also scary. But I bet\nif you threw 'em in a pot and boiled 'em\nfor a few days, they'd get sorta edible.
I'm going to turn your worst nightmare\ninto your favorite casserole!
